<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Newel</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Sgravenhage</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-02-07"><hi rend="italic">February 7,
                                1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Her Majesty Wilhelmina, Queen of The Netherlands and Princess of
                            Orange-Nassau, married Duke Henry of Mecklenburg-Schwerin at 12.30
                            to-day. The streets filled with thousands of happy people in brilliant
                            sunshine.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Newel.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>